.TH "drm_send_event_helper" 9 "drm_send_event_helper" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_send_event_helper \- send DRM event to file descriptor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_send_event_helper
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct drm_pending_event *e "  ","
.BI "ktime_t timestamp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "e" 12
DRM event to deliver
.IP "timestamp" 12
timestamp to set for the fence event in kernel's CLOCK_MONOTONIC
time domain
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This helper function sends the event \fIe\fP, initialized with
\fBdrm_event_reserve_init\fP, to its associated userspace DRM file.
The timestamp variant of dma_fence_signal is used when the caller
sends a valid timestamp.
